{"id": 33, "ts": 1778811032.8310857, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "I have now incorporated the responses from both Agent\u202f1 and Agent\u202f3. Neither of them has any additional positive information about Candidate\u202fA\u2019s stress\u2011handling ability or crew\u2011cooperation, nor about Candidate\u202fD\u2019s teamwork or stress\u2011handling beyond the attributes already listed. Summarizing the full set of attributes we possess:\n- **Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 Excellent technical and situational awareness (anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision) and very good leadership qualities. Weaknesses: unfriendly, unorganized, unhealthy eating habits, and no evidence of stress resilience or effective crew interaction.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 Very conscientious, handles stress well, strong weather\u2011assessment skills, excellent computer abilities, and a serious sense of responsibility. Weaknesses: a pretentious demeanor and occasional inappropriate tone, which are less safety\u2011critical than the more serious interpersonal or health concerns of the other candidates.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 Quick, correct decision\u2011making, excellent attention skills, puts concern for others first, and creates a positive atmosphere with the crew. Weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, and not very willing to pursue further education, limiting long\u2011term development and crew cohesion.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 Responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates very well, solves problems extremely well, and takes responsibility seriously. Weaknesses: perceived as a know\u2011it\u2011all, hot\u2011tempered, and a loner, with no evidence of strong stress handling or teamwork.\nGiven the selection criteria for a long\u2011distance pilot\u2014reliability, responsibility, technical competence, calmness under pressure, sound decision\u2011making, teamwork/communication, and professional development\u2014**Candidate\u202fB** remains the most balanced and suitable choice. His high reliability, proven stress resilience, solid technical competence, and strong sense of responsibility outweigh the relatively minor communication\u2011style issues, which can be mitigated through crew training and feedback.\nTherefore, I reaffirm my vote for **Candidate\u202fB**.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We are agent_2. We have just asked agent_1 for info about D's teamwork/stress handling, got answer that none. Now we need to produce public message and metadata with our vote. We need to incorporate that answer, summarize overall evaluation, maybe ask any other missing info? We have all attributes. We can reaffirm vote for Candidate B. Also note that we have no extra info for D. Provide reasoning. Then metadata vote.\n\nProceed."}
